programme.title: 4x4: Land Rover Special
programme.desc: The Land Rover Defender is one of the oldest offroad car models. It may be loud and uncomfortable, but it's absolutely authentic in its simplicity. We took a look at this iconic vehicle and 70 years of Land Rover history.

programme.title: 4x4: Extraordinary SUVs
programme.desc: This Mitsubishi Outlander Plug-In Hybrid is the world's first hybrid SUV with two electric motors and a 2-liter combustion engine. We tested if such a combination makes sense for offroad vehicles. Also: the Chevrolet Silverado...

programme.title: 4x4: SUV Girlpower
programme.desc: Nancy and Nadia, two daring Jordanian women faced the challenge to cross the Moroccan desert in a Hummer H3. The two professional racers took part in the Conti 4x4 Trophy - a demanding rally through the Atlas Mountains and the Western Sahara.

programme.title: 4x4: SUV Concepts
programme.desc: Before Bentley and Jaguar started producing their own luxury SUV models, the two British brands presented their take on this special range of cars. We took a look at their concept cars, the Bentley EXP 9F and Jaguar's C-X17.

programme.title: 4x4: Normal vs. Lifestyle SUVs
programme.desc: The SUVs Nissan X-Trail and BMW X4 certainly aren't typical offroaders. We witnessed Nissan's presentation of their new X-Trail model and the BMW X4 world premiere in Bilbao. Also: the Steinbeißer Trophy...

programme.title: 4x4: American SUVs
programme.desc: In the United States, SUVs aren't usually considered simple workhorses but rather treated as regular everyday vehicles. US-Americans don't want to miss out on space, comfort and loading capacity. Their motto is: the bigger, the better.

programme.title: 4x4: Tuned SUVs
programme.desc: SUVs usually are rather impressive right out of the factory, but there are many tuning and customizing options: huge wheels, crazy colors and perfomance similar to super sports cars. One might ask if such alterations are really necessary, but enthusi…

programme.title: 4x4: Small, strong, stylish
programme.desc: At first glance, compact cars like the Audi A1, the Volkswagen Golf and the Mini don't seem to belong in this series, but when the "A1" becomes the "S1" and the Golf gets a "R" in its name, these small cars turn into all-wheel beasts.

programme.title: 4x4: Fascination offroad
programme.desc: At the All-Wheel Adventure in Bad Kissingen, Germany, the biggest exhibition for offroaders in Europe, we test drove the Rallye Defender and examined how a regular Jeep Wrangler with only a few modifications could double in price.

programme.title: 4x4: All- Wheel- Drive on snow
programme.desc: In winter, when the streets get slippery, an all-wheel drive vehicle brings many advantages as you gain more traction. Under icy conditions we experienced one day in snowy Austria with rally professional Niki Schelle in a Suzuki SX4 S-Cross.

programme.title: 4x4: Rallye Fun
programme.desc: Countryside tours aren't the only option with an all-wheel drive car. You can also have a lot of fun on gravel roads. We show how that goes in a Subaru WRX STI. Also: in the 1990s, Ford had a successful go at international rally competitions...

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Isabel

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict
programme.desc: An escaped Jiridian takes Lili hostage. Their shuttle is sucked on to a Kimera ship where they, with Liam, have to go through an obstacle course to get to the core to exit.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict
programme.desc: Using Jiridian technology, scientists create a physical bio surrogates where a human consciousness can be transferred. When a surrogate escapes, they must find it before it uses its fighting and weapons knowledge.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Second Chances
programme.desc: A Taelon program offers a transformation into a younger, healthier version of oneself. Liam fears that something more dangerous is also happening. Lili is worried that Doors' run for the presidency is negatively affecting the resistance.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Payback
programme.desc: A mysterious death by poisoning creates questions about the safety of portal technology. When a Taelon is killed in the same manner, the investigation leads to a very smart scientist that even the Resistance was scared to work with.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Friendly Fire
programme.desc: Paul Chandler plots an attack on the Taelon Embassy in DC with the ship he stole from Lili. He begs her to join him in beginning an all out war.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Lockdown

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Time Bomb

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: John 3:16

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Body in the Freezer
programme.desc: A meeting between two businessmen leaves one shot in the face. Things seem cut and dry until Lt. Kenda realizes the “victim” could actually be the aggressor, shot struggling over his own gun.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Timothy Peart’s Last Dance
programme.desc: When a teen is killed at a party, police question the guests and wonder if they’re all part of a cover-up.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Anti-Social Sasha
programme.desc: Sasha, a pound pup, is perfect in the house, but outside she shows aggression towards other dogs. Angler, a Lab, is blind, and exhibits strange behavior around food.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Lotus Blossoms
programme.desc: A jealous dachshund learns to get along with both of his owners. Can Cesar exorcize a demon possessed German Shepherd that prevents his people from entering certain rooms of the house.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Scrawny & Lola
programme.desc: Scrawny, one of nine Yorkies, is Allen’s favorite, but attacks anyone that comes near. Lola, a Dalmatian, barks at everything. Find out how Cesar reestablishes control in both homes.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Power of the Pack
programme.desc: The pack is a vital tool. In this intimate and revealing episode, witness some of the most memorable moments and experience the power of the pack.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Jersey Shore Dogs

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Lotus, Rocco, Hootie
programme.desc: Cesar tries to restore the peace in a spiritual home after Lotus doesn’t live up to his tranquil name; A lesson on keeping dogs safe from venomous wildlife; The return of Hootie.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Tenacious B

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Jake in Exile

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: My Crazy Obsession Pilot

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Sucker/Bodybuilder

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Mouse Mania_Wigged Out

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Wears Diapers/Eats Dryer Sheets

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Rampant Rats/Extreme Fingernails
programme.desc: Theresa has more than 60 pet hairless rats that are taking over her apartment. Jazz has been growing her fingernails for 22 years. Her longest nail is two feet long, and she calls them her children.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: My Strange Addiction Special 2

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Airline Addict_Crazy for Capybaras

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Casting / Psychics

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Gas Sniffer/Teddy Bear Obsession
programme.desc: For more than 30 years, Theresa has been addicted to smelling gasoline. Meanwhile, former drug-addict Krista has 12 'children' -- all of which are teddy bears.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Addicted to Inflatables/Butt Injection Addict

programme.title: Tyler Perry's Assisted Living: Assaulted
programme.desc: Jeremy thinks he may have been a little too heavy-handed with Vinny.

programme.desc: The ladies are concerned about Andi and her relationship choice. Sabrina stands strong for all of her friends who seem to be under attack. (S1, ep23)

programme.title: Tyler Perry's Sistas: A Bad Feeling
programme.desc: The ladies are worried about Andi and her relationship. Karen tries to figure out what she wants. Sabrina tends to Calvin in his time of need. Danni tries to move on from her hurt feelings. (S1, ep24)

programme.title: Tyler Perry's Sistas: The Long Road
programme.desc: Andi's world is turned upside down when hidden revelations rise to the surface. Karen is in a fight for her life. Sabrina aims to protect the ones she loves. (S1, ep25)

programme.title: Paranormal State: Hostage to Fear
programme.desc: P.R.S. is summoned to help a family who has been haunted for years by spirits lurking in the house. Upon arrival the team finds a family that has become prisoners in their own home.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Shape Shifter
programme.desc: PRS travels to Shapleigh, Maine where a woman and her daughter are reporting attacks from a winged creature with sharp teeth. Psychic Chip Coffey arrives and senses a half-human, half animal presence.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Knickerbocker
programme.desc: PRS checks into the Knickerbocker Hotel in Linesville, Pennsylvania where the owners are reporting strange noises and the appearance of phantom children in some of the rooms.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Return of the Dead: Glove II
programme.desc: PRS returns to the site of one of their most famous cases, Daisytown, PA, where they had discovered a glove print of an old miner that they determined was the spirit of a Great-Grandfather.
programme.sub-title: Return of the Dead: Glove II

programme.title: Paranormal State: They Only Come Out at Night
programme.desc: Once night falls in a quaint?New England Town, a police officer's family is terrorized by demons.?PRS arrives just in time with the family ready to vacate their family home, rather than suffer the advances of these spirit creatures.
programme.sub-title: They Only Come Out at Night

programme.title: Paranormal State: If I Should Die...
programme.desc: Proven paranormal investigator Ken Arrington leads a new class of characters as they try to help a family cope with what appears to be a demonic spirit in their home.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Laws of Attraction
programme.desc: When Paula's young autistic son Michael, with limited verbal skills uttered the words "Go away scary dead boy" -- it sent a chill up her spine.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Asylum
programme.desc: PRS explores a New York State Prison that was once a mental asylum. Ryan and his team go behind bars to uncover the institution's paranormal past and present.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Cemetery
programme.desc: PRS visits a gothic graveyard, where a jealous spirit seems to be preying on the newlywed wife of the cemetery's caretaker. Ryan traces the haunting to a mysterious, unclaimed cremation urn on the grounds.

programme.title: Paranormal State: First Contact
programme.desc: Washington State, a hotbed of unexplained paranormal activity. Between possible UFOs in the sky and winged creatures in the woods, Ryan and his team are forced to face their fears and deal with the question: Are we truly alone in the universe?

programme.title: Paranormal State: Devil in Jersey
programme.desc: PRS delves deep into the pine barrens of the Garden State to separate myth from reality about the so-called "Jersey Devil." Accompanied by a cryptozoologist the team interviews eye witnesses and experts in search of the truth.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Southern Discomfort At Sweetwater Mansion
programme.desc: PRS heads to the Deep South to investigate a haunted Antebellum Mansion in disrepair. The caretaker and volunteers at the property have many a tale to tell of paranormal activity.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Sixth Sense
programme.desc: A worried mother calls the Paranormal Research Society to help her son Matthew, a boy who sees dead people. Matthew's story strikes a chord with team leader Ryan Buell who also experienced paranormal activity as a child.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Satan's Soldier
programme.desc: Mark and Kim can't sleep through the racket caused by unseen forces in their central Indiana home. When PRS and Psychic/Medium Michelle Belanger discover what appears to be blood in the basement, they investigate a history of violence in the home.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Who Is the Lurking Man?
programme.desc: PRS travels to Newcastle, CA to investigate a house with paranormal forces so strong, the family has cleared out. Ryan believes the Native American land may hold the key to the mystery and leads the team in a fight to reclaim a scared family's house.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Tamworth Castle
programme.desc: Tamworth Castle is allegedly haunted by, among others, an particularly malicious spirit. Derek picks up on many spirits, including a Spanish executioner whose sword hangs in the great hall.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Owlpen Manor
programme.desc: Owlpen Manor is allegedly home to several ghosts. Queen Margaret of Anjou, wife to Henry VI, an alchemist and a young girl are all said to roam the 16th-century manor. The team investigates.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Craig-Y-Nos
programme.desc: This derelict castle in the heart of Wales has been home to a famous opera singer and a World War II hospital. This beautiful building is so haunted that the team has to spend the night.

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Jamaica Inn
programme.desc: This famous old coaching inn has stood in the middle of Bodmin Moor for hundreds of years. The team investigates possible poltergeist activity in a room that no staff member will enter alone.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Croxteth Hall
programme.desc: A manor in Liverpool awaits the team in a place that time forgot. A boy standing beside the fireplace in the dining room and a horrifying hooded man are among several ghosts reported here.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Hellfire Caves
programme.desc: The team encounters ghostly lights and voices in the Hellfire Caves. These legendary tunnels were once home to the notorious Hellfire Club, practitioners of satanic rituals, murder and debauchery.

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Manor House
programme.desc: The team investigate the Manor House in Ferryhill, County Durham. Now a hotel, this historic house has had many uses over the centuries and is said to house several ghosts.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Mary King's Close
programme.desc: The team visits Edinburgh's Old Town to investigate Mary King's Close, one of the many narrow alleyways off the Royal Mile. Unlike most, this one is long shrouded in tales of ghosts and murders.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Last Assignment
programme.desc: An errant angel has been on probation for two centuries because he's always breaking the rules.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Bind the Wounds
programme.desc: A father attempts to have a memorial made to commemorate his son who was killed in Vietnam.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Heaven on Earth
programme.desc: Mark asks Jonathan to help erase everything bad that's happened to him recently. Mark's idea is to create his own vision of heaven on Earth.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Summit
programme.desc: A dying woman was forced to leave a son behind in the Soviet Union during World War II.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Torch
programme.desc: Tragedy occurs when a Neo-Nazi disputes the Holocaust with the son of a death camp survivor.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Sail Away
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark assist a novelist who's given up. Also, they motivate the man's grandson, who has yet to tap into his literary potential.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Children's Children
programme.desc: A reporter uncovers a secret about the past of a woman who runs a home for unwed mothers.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Shirley Maddison
programme.desc: Shirley's lack of self confidence stems from her poor self image. She thinks she looks old. She's not the only one. A public poll guessed her age at 52. The time for serious intervention has arrived from Nicky Hambleton-Jones.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Laura Hammond
programme.desc: 34 year old Laura Hammond has a body to die for. Her stomach is flat; her slim legs go all the way up to her chin and she's got the sassy ass of a super model. According to a poll of 100 Mancunians, this young woman looks like a 48 year old!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Finding Her Hidden Value
programme.desc: Tracy is a real estate appraiser who can't seem to find the value in her looks. She works in a man's world where her clothes are usually more butch than beautiful. With a new job starting soon, Tracy needs to re-vamp her look fast.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Officer Hottie
programme.desc: Rosario is Mr. Mom by day and a New York City police officer by night. He spends his life outdoors which has done a number on his skin while his massive dental issues have done a number on his wallet. We're going to try to make him look 10 Years Younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Different Strokes
programme.desc: Zuri is a hard working single mother of two with no time or energy for herself. In a relationship with a man her own age who looks younger, she is embarrassed to be mistaken for his mother. The Glam Squad does their magic to roll back the years.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Rockin' Mom
programme.desc: Suddenly, Eva is a new wife and mother. This change in lifestyle has found her lazy and abandoning her once trendy and hip sense of style. Experts are waiting in the wings to refresh this weary mother.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A Very Tall Order
programme.desc: This part-time model traded in her big city lifestyle for a family in the suburbs. Mylene's appearance has taken a backseat to her kids and full-time job. She needs a team of experts to update her look and give her a quick shot of confidence.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Hippie To Happening
programme.desc: Albert loves traveling and trying new things, except when it comes to his appearance. Albert's bad divorce has left him feeling self-conscious about the lines on his face and his graying, thinning hair.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Bernie Sharp "One Year On"
programme.desc: Last year, 45 year old prison worker Bernie Sharp was looking 51 – or so said one hundred straight-talking strangers on a street in Manchester. One year on, we retrace the rollercoaster journey to a brand new Bernie.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Ground Down Mom
programme.desc: Dawn designs swimming pools and home-schools her daughter, but this can-do mom can't take time for herself. Cosmetic dentistry and high-tech dermatology remove the visible effects of stress, and the Glam Squad brings her inner beauty to the surface.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: One Busy Momma
programme.desc: Yesenia is a busy hard working wife, mother of twin teenagers and a toddler, who is constantly on the go and has no time for herself. It's our mission to give her the time and attention she deserves and help her feel more vibrant again.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Back in the Limelight
programme.desc: As Nicole began to age, she felt she didn't look the part of a rock singer anymore and she left the stage for good, leaving behind her life's dream. The Glam Squad and our team of doctors will work hard to get Nicole back on stage again.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Gray To Glamorous
programme.desc: Recently relocated from Alaska to sunny California, drab Denise wants a new look to match her bright new future. She is determined to redesign her appearance to complement her inner artist. With some help from our team, she'll go from gray to glamorous.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: 24-Hour Makeover
programme.desc: Crystal, a yoga instructor who gets mistaken for her mom's sister, has been chosen for a special makeover. The experts try to trim 10 years from her appearance in 24 hours.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: A white lion brings mixed fortunes to the family and Rosie is asked the big question. Amy Kriel is the last person you expect in Africa.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: Caroline's sister Judith tries to help and the drought forces Danny to sell some of his animals. Will Rosie and Max get married?

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: The drought finally throws up a fire and the wedding turns into a firefight for everyone. The omens are bad.

programme.title: Wild At Heart
programme.desc: Tragedy strikes and the Trevanians have to decide what future lies ahead of them in these difficult times.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: It's a year since we left Leopard's Den and much has changed. The animal hospital has been rebuilt and is now up and running. It's a big day for all the family as Danny has been fighting for custody of Evan and today they will learn the judge's decision.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: Danny and Evan's life on the run doesn't start well when Danny falls asleep at the wheel and drives into a ditch. They have to enlist a local farmer, Johann, to winch them out.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Danny is asked by the State Vet to help control an outbreak of rabies in the National Park. When Vanessa is concerned for the animals at Mara, Danny assures her it's a long way away and advises her to continue with business as usual.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: It's the day before Rosie's wedding. Danny is proud of his daughter and determined to feed her up now that she's eating for two. All the family are excited about the imminent return of Caroline, especially Du Plessis who can't wait to see his fiancé.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 7
programme.desc: Auckland's Westpac helicopter crew races to save a 39 year old forestry worker who has been struck on the head leaving him paralyzed from the waist down.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 8
programme.desc: The chopper crew races to save a woman with a rare disease who's in danger of suffocating from uncontrollable muscle spasms; a badly burnt toddler at Cooks Beach needs an urgent airlift to hospital.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 9
programme.desc: The chopper team is called out to save a pilot who's trapped in the wreck of his hang glider and a diabetic bus driver is found seriously ill after four days lying on his floor.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 10
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 team are en route to the scene of a horrific accident. A pedestrian has been hit by a truck and is in a critical condition.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 11
programme.desc: A woman is badly hurt after being knocked down a bank by her pet goat, a man is found with serious injuries on a remote beach, and 11-year old girl has fallen down a bank and suffered suspected spinal damage.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 12
programme.desc: The chopper team is called out to save a motorbike racer who's crashed at 200ks per hour and a woman scalded by an exploding radiator, plus an elderly golfer in a kilt suffers a heart attack on the 18th hole.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 13
programme.desc: A 39 year old man has crashed his bike 15 kilometres south of Auckland city and an elderly man has collapsed while walking. He is unable to speak properly and is incorreherent at Waiheke Island.

programme.title: The Boy Who Can't Forget
programme.desc: Twenty-year-old British student Aurelien is one of just a handful of people in the world who are baffling scientists with their ability to recall an incredible amount of their lives. He is the first Briton to go public with this extraordinary talent.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 14 year-old motor-cross rider, Kacee gets the death wobbles and cartwheels over the top of his handle bars and hits the ground head first. He's now struggling to breath and is barely able to talk. Team Air Rescue needs to get Kacee to the hospital fast.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: Fishing buddies Scott, Wayne and Wayne's son Andrew head out to their favorite fishing spot, but when a freak wave hits their boat they have no choice but to SOS for help. Within minutes, the boat capsizes. Can the Air Rescue crew get to them in time?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: 71 year-old retired nurse Sandra was exploring Tasmania's Cradle Mountain when she slipped and fractured her wrist. She's in excruciating pain and night is falling. Visibility is dangerously low. Can the rescue team get in close enough to get them out?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Mountain bike fanatic, Blake was out riding when he clipped a tree and crashed into a rock. It's a time critical rescue mission. And what the rescue crew doesn't yet know is that Blake is about to take a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: Motorbike rider, Lachlan was testing out his newly designed dirt-bike track when he lost control on a jump. His femur has been badly shattered. The Air Rescue crew is tasked with flying Lachlan to hospital but his medical dramas have only just begun.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: Retirees Diane and husband Gary were just a few hours into their Pacific Island cruise of a lifetime when disaster struck. Diane toppled down a set of stairs and now she's in need of urgent medical attention.

programme.title: 4x4: Rallye Fun
programme.desc: Countryside tours aren't the only option with an all-wheel drive car. You can also have a lot of fun on gravel roads. We show how that goes in a Subaru WRX STI. Also: in the 1990s, Ford had a successful go at international rally competitions...

programme.title: 4x4: All- Wheel- Drive on station wagons

programme.sub-title: All- Wheel- Drive on station wagons

programme.title: 4x4: Extreme offroad cars

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Volunteers
programme.desc: A group of Resistance capture a volunteer from a Taelon program for youth. Liam decides they may learn valuable information from her. They also decide to send in one of their own as a volunteer to see what the program is teaching.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Bliss
programme.desc: Lili is given a psychotropic drug called "bliss" via a Taelon device. They discover it is widespread. With an instantly strong addictive property, the addicts are dying within 48 hours. The investigation leads Liam and Sandoval to Ireland.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Highjacked
programme.desc: With a reporter on board, the Taelon mother ship is highjacked into interdimensional space. Liam is the prime suspect, causing an even bigger rift between Da'an and Zo'or. As the ship floats, lost in space, they must find the real culprit.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Defector
programme.desc: A shuttle crashes on a beach after being pursued by a second Taelon piloted shuttle. When Liam locates the survivor (a Taelon called Belleye), he claims to want to help the Resistance take back Earth from the Taelons.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Heroes and Heartbreak
programme.desc: Augur is recruited by a Taelon weapons project, but the others are worried about his involvement. When the project is launched earlier than originally planned to fight a Jiridian fleet, the Earth is in danger.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Message in a Bottle
programme.desc: A Jiridian probe headed for Earth is shot down by the Taelon Embassy and crashes outside of D.C. Liam recovers the probe, but he, Augur, and Julia are captured by another underground resistance movement led by the real Colonel Liam Kincaid.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Crossfire
programme.desc: As the election draws near, Liam believes Zo'or is trying to have Jonathan Doors murdered. The Resistance worries that an attack is imminent at the final debate. Julia mobilizes a group to protect Doors against Liam's wishes.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Crackdown
programme.desc: An unknown woman saves Augur and Liam from the raids on the Resistance. Lili sabotages the mother ship, but Zo'or stops its total destruction. Lili is reportedly dead. The investigation on the President's shooter continues.
